🔌 Digital Pins (0–13)

Digital pins can be configured as either inputs or outputs.


LOW  = 0V
HIGH = 5V


Used for:

* LEDs
* Push buttons
* Relays
* Digital sensors



🎚️ PWM Pins

Available PWM pins:


3, 5, 6, 9, 10, 11


PWM (Pulse Width Modulation) allows Arduino to simulate analog output using digital pins.

Example duty cycles:


25% Duty Cycle ≈ 1.25V average
50% Duty Cycle ≈ 2.50V average
75% Duty Cycle ≈ 3.75V average


Used for:

* LED brightness control
* Motor speed control
* Servo control

---

📈 Analog Input Pins (A0–A5)

Used for reading analog voltages.

Built-in 10-bit ADC conversion:


0V → 0
5V → 1023


Used for:

* Temperature sensors
* Potentiometers
* Light sensors
* Gas sensors



🔄 UART Serial Communication

| Pin | Function |
| --- | -------- |
| 0   | RX       |
| 1   | TX       |

RX (Receive)

Receives data from external devices.

TX (Transmit)

Sends data to external devices.

Communication example:


Device TX ─────► Arduino RX
Arduino TX ────► Device RX


Used for:

* Serial Monitor
* Bluetooth modules
* GPS modules
* GSM modules

---

